{{Infobox person | name = Levent Karahan <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = [[File:Levent karahan.jpg|275px]] <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1966|10|25}} | parents = Cemil Karahan, Meral Karahan | children = Deniz Karahan, Lili Meral Karahan | alma_mater = [[Drummers Focus]], School Of Audio Engineering Institute | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = Music technology entrepreneur | years_active = | known_for = Founder of JAY Entertainment, YOOM, REGGAEinc, UMIJam, EVEARA | notable_works = | website = {{URL|www.leventkarahan.com}} }}
'''Levent Karahan''' (born 25 October 1966) is a [[Laz language|Laz]] music technology entrepreneur, a pioneer of digital music distribution, founder and chief executive officer of various organizations such as JAY Entertainment, YOOM, REGGAEinc, UMIJam, and EVEARA, a member of the Recording Industry Association Of Jamaica (RIAJam) and the Reggae Academy & Awards.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VxMEAAAAMBAJ|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=2008-03-15|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/615784-Levent-Karahan|title=Levent Karahan|website=Discogs|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yardflex.com/archives/002152.html|title=Half Pint unveils "NO STRESS EXPRESS"|website=YardFlex.com|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite web|url=http://www.bumbablog.com/artist/?art=615784|title=Levent Karahan {{!}} BUMBABlog|website=BUMBABLOG|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{cite web|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Levent-Karahan/625775761|title=Levent Karahan {{!}} Reggae Inc {{!}} ZoomInfo.com|website=ZoomInfo|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.halfpintmusic.com/news/category/no-stress-express/|title=No Stress Express : Half Pint Music|website=www.halfpintmusic.com|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref>
==Early life and background== Levent Karahan was born in [[Arhavi]], [[Turkey]] on October 25, 1966. In 1972 his parents migrated to Munich, Germany. Inspired by [[The Beatles]], he decided to pursue music, starting out as a drummer. Going forward he became involved in songwriting, [[audio engineer]]ing, [[Music production (music industry)|music production]], music video production, and [[music management]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /> Some of his compositions and music productions such as ''Love Is The Only Way'', ''The Box Song'', and ''Butterfly'' resulted in success<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zajumaj.pl/pobierz/IK576w3ZAFE/david-o-joseph-butterfly-radio-versionmp4/|title=David O. Joseph - Butterfly (Radio Version).mp4 - zajumaj.pl|website=zajumaj.pl|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref> and in 2003 ''Butterfly'' made it to the Top 100 in Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vidinfo.org/video/57409255/butterflyz-up-town-top-ranking|title=Butterflyz - Up Town Top Ranking|website=YouTube|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref> In 2002, he migrated to Jamaica and lived there for 8 years until he returned to Turkey in 2010.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://snwmf.com/phorum/read.php?1,157651,157698|title=Kingston this weekend|website=snwmf.com|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.travelbook.tv/channel/UCn2vpNVykX0HMR9SzSsQHLg/CDIQAQ|title=travelbook|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
==Career== Levent explored the business side of the music universe subsequently becoming a Label Manager of Toxic (Mambo/[[Sony]]) in 1997. In 1998, he became A&R Manager of [[Columbia (Sony)]], and a publisher with [[Universal Music Group|Universal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediabiz.de/musik/firmen/universal-music-publishing-group-germany/angeschlossene-verlage/23680 |title=MusikWoche &#124; Universal Music Publishing Group (Germany) &#124; Produktionspartner national |publisher=Mediabiz.de |date= |accessdate=2016-04-21}}</ref> In December 1998, he launched Talent'99, a talent show case for the German music industry. In 1999, he founded JAY Entertainment, a venture into the earliest online music labels.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" />
In the year 2000, he became Director Business Development of People Sound, a European mainstream music portal, and founded YOOM, which is claimed to be the world's first standardized software for digital music downloads.<ref name=":3" /> In 2001, YOOM merged with 24-7 Entertainment (MediaSaturn/Metro) which later became a mainstream digital entertainment company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://247entertainment.com/Press/247_Reggaeinc_190707.pdf|title=247entertainment|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2003, he founded REGGAEinc, the first Reggae content aggregation and digital Reggae distribution company operating out of Jamaica.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20100621/ent/ent5.html|title=Changing the face of reggae|website=www.jamaica-gleaner.com|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/entertainment/Reggae-Inc-staying-on-top-of-the-music-game_7600560-staying-on-top-of-the-music-game_7600560|title=Reggae-Inc-staying-on-top-of-the-music|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.jamaicans.com/reggaeincreggaesumfest2007/|title=Reggaeincreggaesumfest2007|website=Jamaicans.com News and Events Archives|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mp3newsong.info/new/song/mp3/reggaeinc-tvj-entertainment-report.html|title=Reggaeinc Tvj Entertainment Report Mp3 Download {{!}} Mp3 New Song|website=www.mp3newsong.info|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reviewourwebsites.org/domain/reggaeinc.com|title=reggaeinc.com - HOME I REGGAEinc Digital Reggae Distribution|website=www.reviewourwebsites.org|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref>
In 2007, Karahan became a member of the Recording Industry Association Of Jamaica (RIAJam) and the Reggae Academy & Awards, he was co-founder and president of UMIJam (The United Music Industry Of Jamaica),<ref>{{cite web|last=Writer |first=Staff |url=http://archives.jamaicans.com/page/1338/ |title=Jamaicans.com News and Events Archives - Page 1338 of 1473 - Archives of past news, announcements, press releases and events |publisher=Archives.jamaicans.com |date=2007-07-13 |accessdate=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Published 19-May-10 |url=http://www.trinijunglejuice.com/tjjnews/articles/1392/1/Reggae-Inc-making-a-difference-in-the-Jamaican-Music-Industry/Page1.html |title=Reggae Inc. making a difference in the Jamaican Music Industry |publisher=Trinijunglejuice.com |date= |accessdate=2016-04-21}}</ref> the umbrella organization of the Jamaican music industry from 2008-2010, initiated by the Jamaican government and the European Union.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tv.mona.uwi.edu/united-music-industry-jamaica-case-study-0|title=The United Music Industry of Jamaica - A Case Study {{!}} UWItv|website=tv.mona.uwi.edu|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mona.uwi.edu/conferences/2008/globalreggae/schedule4.php|title=Global Reggae Conference 2008 {{!}} The University of the West Indies at Mona, Jamaica|website=www.mona.uwi.edu|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref>
In 2013, he joined forces with WAVTEQ, a fast growing innovative international software company with its software development hub based in Ireland, with the common goal to produce a competitive digital music distribution software. In 2015, they incorporated EVEARA in [[Cork (Ireland)|Cork, Ireland]], a game changer in the digital music distribution solution market.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.solocheck.ie/Irish-Company/Eveara-Limited-560767|title=Eveara Ltd - Irish Company Info and Credit Scores - SoloCheck|website=www.solocheck.ie|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref>
